The authentication types a service client supports is defined in AbstractAzureServiceClientBuilderFactory.getAuthenticationDescriptors(Object). If a credential is resolved successfully, the AbstractAzureServiceClientBuilderFactory.credentialConfigured flag will be set to true.

    • configureConnectionString

      protected void configureConnectionString(com.azure.messaging.servicebus.ServiceBusClientBuilder.ServiceBusSessionProcessorClientBuilder builder)
      Description copied from class: AbstractAzureServiceClientBuilderFactory
      Configure the connection string to the builder if the credential is not yet configured. It will try to resolve a connection string from the AzureProperties, if it is a ConnectionStringProvider instance. If no connection string found from the AzureProperties, it will check if any ServiceConnectionStringProvider is provided and get the connection string from the provider if set. If a connection string is resolved successfully, the AbstractAzureServiceClientBuilderFactory.credentialConfigured flag will be set to true.
      Overrides:
      configureConnectionString in class AbstractAzureServiceClientBuilderFactory<T>
      Parameters:
      builder - The service client builder.
